title: VFS creates duplicate files on GDrive with LibreOffice
body:

#### What is the problem you are having with rclone?

When saving a file from LibreOffice into an rclone mount of Google Drive, two duplicate flies will be created in the google drive folder as rclone does not seem to keep up when multiple temporary files are written/deleted at once.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10167247/126422775-26fccb9f-1d11-49ad-85fb-78104c4e3bd9.png)



#### What is your rclone version (output from `rclone version`)

```
rclone v1.56.0
- os/version: ubuntu 20.04 (64 bit)
- os/kernel: 5.11.0-22-generic (x86_64)
- os/type: linux
- os/arch: amd64
- go/version: go1.16.5
- go/linking: static
- go/tags: none
```

#### Which OS you are using and how many bits (e.g. Windows 7, 64 bit)

Ubuntu 20.04 LTS x64

#### Which cloud storage system are you using? (e.g. Google Drive)

Google Drive


#### The command you were trying to run (e.g. `rclone copy /tmp remote:tmp`)

```
  /usr/bin/rclone mount \
    --config=%h/.config/rclone/rclone.conf \
    --drive-skip-gdocs \
    --buffer-size 72M \
    --drive-chunk-size 64M \
    --vfs-cache-mode writes \
    --vfs-cache-max-size 1G \
    %i: %h/mnt/%i
```

config just contains secret+token for Google Drive

#### A log from the command with the `-vv` flag (e.g. output from `rclone -vv copy /tmp remote:tmp`)
